&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Heat oil in a cast iron skillet. Add garlic, green beans, and black pepper. Cover tightly and shake the pan to coat them in the garlic and pepper. Cook over medium heat.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;After 2 minutes, shake up or stir the beans so they don&amp;#39;t burn, and cook 2 minutes longer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If using almonds, add them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add fish sauce (and a bit of water if the green beans are burning).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Cook for a final 2 minutes or until the beans are cooked to the desired consistency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
